    "feat": {
        "name": "Geologic Attunement",
        "type": "stat_block_section",
        "subtype": "feat",
        "text": "You tune to the earth and stone around you, extending your senses through it in rippling waves. You gain tremorsense (imprecise) in your kinetic aura. Once per round, you can Point Out a creature you can sense with tremorsense as a free action.\n\n---\n\n**Level (13th)** The tremorsense becomes precise.",
        "level": 1,
        "action_type": {
            "type": "stat_block_section",
            "subtype": "action_type",
            "name": "One Action"
        },
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Earth",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 55,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 455",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 455",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 455,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "c0ece3ed45c1990f2753e00341d335da",
                "text": "Effects with the earth trait either manipulate or conjure earth. Those that manipulate earth have no effect in an area without earth. Creatures with this trait consist primarily of earth or have a connection to magical earth.  \n  \nThese planes are mostly solid. Travelers arriving upon an earth plane risk suffocation if they don\u2019t reach a cavern or some other air pocket within the plane\u2019s solid matter. Creatures who can\u2019t burrow are entombed in the plane\u2019s substance and must attempt to dig their way toward an air pocket. Air creatures are ill at ease, as they rarely have the space to move freely through even the loftiest warrens."
            },
            {
                "name": "Impulse",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Rage of Elements",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Rage of Elements pg. 15",
                            "alt": "Rage of Elements pg. 15",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 205
                        },
                        "page": 15,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 205
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "f83779b12b3f1e7096ae9a32ca68ea4f",
                "text": "The primary magical actions kineticists use are called impulses. You can use an impulse only if your kinetic aura is active and channeling that element, and only if you have a hand free to shape the elemental flow. The impulse trait means the action has the concentrate trait unless another ability changes this. If an impulse allows you to choose an element, you can choose any element you're channeling, and the impulse gains that element's trait.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "concentrate",
                        "alt": "concentrate",
                        "game-obj": "Traits",
                        "aonid": 32
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Kineticist",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Rage of Elements",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Rage of Elements pg. 237",
                            "alt": "Rage of Elements pg. 237",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 205
                        },
                        "page": 237,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 205
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "721afce0c1e219e9edd3709db105bb4e",
                "text": "This indicates abilities from the kineticist class.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "kineticist",
                        "alt": "kineticist",
                        "game-obj": "Classes",
                        "aonid": 23
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Primal",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 134,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 460",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 460",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 460,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "60a4f011afd1e0fac8211bd01108d104",
                "text": "This magic comes from the primal tradition, connecting to the natural world and instinct. Anything with this trait is magical.  \n  \nA creature with this trait is primarily constituted of or has a strong connection to primal magic."
            },
            {
                "name": "Stance",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 152,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 139",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 139",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 139,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "9035508c239ef7305f5fce73844742d8",
                "text": "A stance is a general combat strategy that you enter by using an action with the stance trait, and you remain in for some time. A stance lasts until you get knocked out, until its requirements (if any) are violated, until the encounter ends, or until you use a stance action again, whichever comes first. After you take an action with the stance trait, you can\u2019t take another one for 1 round. You can enter or be in a stance only in encounter mode. You can Dismiss a stance."
            }
        ],
